    ImageObserver, MenuContainer, Serializable, Accessible, RootPaneContainer, WindowConstants
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    MultiInputDialog

    public abstract class AbstractMultiInputDialog
extends JDialog
    Flexible generic dialog to prompt the user typing input parameters. This abstract class includes the logic from original JUMP MultiInputDialog but does not layout components, which is done by implementing classes.
    Author:
    Michaël Michaud
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
